comments.body:
Engine-WG reviewed this issue, and we believe it's a bug. This happens to general exceptions thrown from expressions (e.g. `1/0`), from method invocations, or from parameter binding failures:
```
function Get-Error1 {[CmdletBinding()]Param() 1; 1/0; 2}
function Get-Error2 {[CmdletBinding()]Param() 1; Get-Command -NonExistParam; 2}
function Get-Error3 {[CmdletBinding()]Param() 1; [string]::Copy(1,2,3,4); 2}
```
